$$ \begin{aligned}
\mathrm{KL}(p \| q) &=-\int p(\mathbf{x}) \ln q(\mathbf{x}) \mathrm{d} \mathbf{x}-\left(-\int p(\mathbf{x}) \ln p(\mathbf{x}) \mathrm{d} \mathbf{x}\right) \\
&=-\int p(\mathbf{x}) \ln \left\{\frac{q(\mathbf{x})}{p(\mathbf{x})}\right\} \mathrm{d} \mathbf{x} \\ D_{\mathrm{KL}}[p(x): q(x)] &= \int p(x) \log \left(\frac{p(x)}{q(x)}\right) \mathrm{d} x \end{aligned} $$
